comments.text: I recently noticed that when issuing a "make clean" in the js/src directory, the file editline/libeditline.a is not deleted. When I first build a 64 bit shell, then clean/autoconf/reconfigure and then attempt to build a 32 bit shell, the build fails due to that file still being present (once I delete it, build works fine).
comments.raw_text: I recently noticed that when issuing a "make clean" in the js/src directory, the file editline/libeditline.a is not deleted. When I first build a 64 bit shell, then clean/autoconf/reconfigure and then attempt to build a 32 bit shell, the build fails due to that file still being present (once I delete it, build works fine).
